The closure of the highway is imminent, after suspected cases of infection caused by self-driving trips. As at 14:00 pm on 23 January, the expressway out of Wuhan was closed

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
Gongjialing Toll Station, Wue Expressway, Hongshan district, Wuhan City, Hubei Province, has been stuck in traffic for an hour and a half

By Chen Liang, Lixiyin, and Wang Jingyi, CAIJING reporters

Editor | Shi Zhiliang

In one day on January 22nd, there were 62 new cases of COVID-19 pneumonia in Wuhan. With the further spread of pneumonia in Wuhan, a number of professionals before the proposal of a complete closure of the Wuhan Public Transport System, finally become a reality.

Wuhan's COVID-19 pneumonia epidemic prevention and Control Headquarters announced at 2:00 a.m. on January 23,2020, from 10:00 on January 23, the city's public transport, subway, ferry, long-distance passenger services suspended; Airports and railway stations are temporarily closed from the Han corridor. Recovery time will be announced later.

At about 2 p.m. on January 23, CCTV reporters learned from the Hubei Provincial Highway Administration that the entrances to Gongjialing, Xiaojunshan, Hannan, Beihu, Hanayama, Baiquan, Qinglong and Xihu stations in Hubei Province were closed. The Beijing–Hong Kong–Macau Expressway of the Toll Gates at Wuhan West, Wuhan North, Caidian District and Yong'an will be closed. Other highway crossings out of Wuhan have also been closed.

In the outside world, Wuhan can only enter the city can not leave the city, the implementation of the "city" measures, is a helpless move, although it will bring a lot of inconvenience to the lives of citizens, but is conducive to the investigation and control of the epidemic. A passenger on his way back to China told Caijing that they had not been told they could not stop at Hankou. "It's still a one-way order, in and out. "

From the morning of January 23, the public transport system leaving Wuhan is gradually being shut down. Wuhan Airport planned 629 flights in and out of the port on Jan. 23, according to Airsavvi. As at 1305 hours, 412 sorties had been cancelled. Completed 66 outbound flights, the last outbound flight CZ356, Destination Guangzhou, departure time 12:55.

Wuhan Tianhe Airport News Center middle-level cadres told the "finance and economics" reporter, Wuhan Tianhe Airport is not closed, still in operation. As at 1000 hours, 20 sorties were in and 45 were out. CAIJING reporter recently learned that at present passengers can not enter Wuhan Tianhe Airport terminal, landing passengers can exit the terminal.

Highway is an important choice for many people in Wuhan to leave Wuhan. By the middle of 2019, Wuhan had more than 3.2 million vehicles and millions of daily driving trips. CAIJING reporter learned that since Wuhan began to implement the investigation and control of a major epidemic at the entrance to and exit from the city yesterday, there has been a relatively obvious queuing situation at highway inspection points, with an average queuing time of about 30 minutes.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
Buses in Wuhan are almost out of service

But it's also being shut down. CCTV reporter learned from the Hubei Provincial Highway Management Department, gongjialing in Hubei Province, Xiaojunshan, Hannan, North Lake, Hanayama, Baiquan, Qinglong, West Lake station entrance closed. The Beijing–Hong Kong–Macau Expressway of the Toll Gates at Wuhan West, Wuhan North, Caidian District and Yong'an will be closed. Other highway crossings out of Wuhan have also been closed. Some People Sigh: This is the real "Tucheng" , has not left Wuhan people, the next can only stay in the local.

Some choose to leave Wuhan, others choose to stay behind actively. "I will not leave Wuhan at this time, " a local reporter stationed on the front line told Caijing. Although the situation in Wuhan is now grim, the central committee and the Wuhan Municipal Government decided to close down the city, to keep the virus from spreading to other cities. Wuhan is now a strong man's determination to break the wrist.

#Hours before the siege, thousands of people boarded planes to leave the city

In response to the outbreak, Xiamen Airlines, China Eastern Airlines (600115.sh/00670.HK/NYSE:CEA）、南方航空（600029..sh/01055.HK/）等航司从昨晚至今晨一直在开会讨论航班调整计划。).

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
Wuhan Tianhe Airport on the morning of Jan. 23

Xiamen Airlines staff told the "financial" reporter, Xiamen Airlines has January 22, Wuhan Flight Adjustment Plan to adopt the cancellation policy. Xiamen Airlines canceled some flights in and out of Wuhan on January 23, such as flights from Hangzhou to Wuhan at 8:15 and from Wuhan to Hangzhou at 11:00.

After the management meeting in the early morning resolution, China Eastern Airlines on January 23, China Eastern Airlines, Shanghai Airlines actually fly part of the flights into and out of Wuhan, involving 20 sorties. For example, 6:55 Shanghai Pudong to Wuhan, 10:25 Wuhan to Shanghai Hongqiao, etc. . CAIJING reporter learned that in the early hours of January 23, China Eastern Airlines Wuhan outbound flights have 7, a total of 883 people; Wuhan Inbound Flights 8 flights, a total of 440 people.

China Southern Airlines January 23,10:00 after all flights out of Wuhan cancelled. In addition, China Southern Airlines also canceled some inbound flights. Flights to and from Wuhan were cancelled, with 107 flights cancelled.

A reporter from CAIJING 601111.sh/00753.HK）询问相关情况，目前中国国航尚未就涉及武汉的航班情况作出表态。 .

Wuhan Airport planned 629 flights in and out of the port on Jan. 23, according to Airsavvi. As at 1305 hours, 412 sorties had been cancelled. 37 inbound flights completed. Last inbound flight CA8244, originating from Guiyang, landed at 13:01. Completed 66 outbound flights, the last outbound flight CZ356, Destination Guangzhou, departure time on January 23 at 12:55.

Wuhan Airport Departure Flights Destination: Guangzhou, Paris, Chengdu, Bangkok, Fuzhou, Hong Kong, Boracay, Lanzhou, Lhasa, Xining. Inbound flights depart from Guangzhou, Chongqing, Taiyuan, Chengdu, Bangkok, Xiamen, Sanya, Wenzhou, Ho Chi Minh, Hong Kong, Guiyang, Xi'an, Ensch, Lanzhou, Beijing, Shanghai, Kunming, Linfen, Tianjin, Haikou, Bali, Ningbo, Yangon, Fuzhou, Hangzhou, Quanzhou, Shenzhen, Pougy, Qingdao.

Wuhan Tianhe Airport News Center Staff stressed that Wuhan Airport is not closed, still in operation. At present, the airport in the Organization of Network car, bus protection of passengers travel. It is reported that the airport has set up a two-way temperature measurement import and export, all staff are wearing masks. The passengers at the scene were wearing masks as far as their eyes could see.

China Eastern Airlines flight crew involved in the Wuhan Route, Wuhan Airport ground staff has been fully issued masks, can be worn throughout the work process, other routes staff also all wear masks, do a good job of personal protection.

In the region receiving incoming flights from Wuhan, the airline has also taken steps. A staff member of the China Eastern Aviation Ground Service Department told Caijing that at Shanghai Hongqiao and Pudong airports, China Eastern Airlines Ground Service arranged special personnel, special vehicles and special equipment to ensure wuhan-related flights, and specifically upgraded protective and disinfection measures, protect the safety of passengers and staff.

Although airlines have canceled most flights involving Wuhan, but after 10:00 still a small number of flights from Wuhan Tianhe Airport Take Off. For example, 10:00 Wuhan to Harbin, 10:15 Wuhan to Xining, 10:15 Wuhan to Lhasa, 10:40 Wuhan to Nanning, 11:05 Wuhan to Xining, 11:30 Wuhan to Paris.

At the same time, travel restrictions began at Wuhan Railway Station. Passengers trying to get in and out of Wuhan were stopped. Passengers from other places to Wuhan could stop and leave.

A passenger on his way back to China told Caijing that they had not been told not to stop at Hankou and that the order was one-way. Passengers arriving at Hankou station at around 11 am on January 23 told Caijing that there were no special security measures when they left the station and "no one took my temperature" . The above-mentioned passengers said that no passengers can be seen, leaving the car only passengers and crew, the entrance to the station, the subway entrance has been closed.

After leaving the station, there was a queue of hundreds of people for a taxi, and the above-mentioned passengers finally chose to cycle nearly 5 km back home.

Can Roads be effectively controlled?

"people should not leave Wuhan without special reasons. The airport and railway stations are temporarily closed from the Han corridor, " Caijing noted, the announcement, issued in the early hours of January 23 by the Wuhan's COVID-19 pneumonia prevention and control command, did not mention the closure of highways, state roads and other roads, leading some to believe that the "closure" of the city was incomplete.

According to local people, after the news of the city closure was announced, self-driving became the only option for people in Wuhan to leave, causing congestion on many roads at one time. According to the current regulations of the headquarters, Wuhan does not restrict vehicles from entering or leaving the city, but it is necessary to check the body temperature of people inside the vehicles and whether they are carrying live or wild animals.

This regulation will be implemented from January 22, as follows: Police officers wearing protective masks and gloves ask the driver to open the trunk to check whether there are live animals and wild animals on board; Two Health and epidemic prevention personnel wearing white protective clothing, holding a temperature gun, one by one for testing and screening. Once it is confirmed that the vehicle is not carrying live animals or wild animals, the driver and passengers in the vehicle will be allowed to pass as soon as their body temperature is normal.

Since Wuhan began to implement the investigation and control of a major epidemic at the entrance to and exit from the city yesterday, there has been a relatively obvious queuing situation at highway inspection points, with an average queuing time of about 30 minutes.

According to a report by the wuhan-based Local Media Changjiang Net, the People's police are already short-staffed, and the functional departments of the district governments, such as the Transportation Bureau, the culture and Tourism Bureau, the garden and Forestry Bureau, the Health Bureau and other units, have sent staff, a vehicle inspection on the highway.

There have been no restrictions on Hubei's "a" plates leaving the city, and the checks have not been Flawless. Mr. Liu left Wuhan on the Hancai Expressway at about 9 a.m. on Jan. 23. "No one checked his temperature, and there was no one on the way, " he told Caijing, "There are a lot of highways out of Wuhan, " he said, referring to the city's important external transport links to Yichang, Shiyan, Xi'an and Beijing.

According to the China business daily, at around 9:00 am on January 23, vehicles leaving the Han and Cai expressway, one of the major highways out of Wuhan, were queuing in large numbers. To 9:30 am, the naked eye has been difficult to see the end of the queue of vehicles, vehicles have been waiting for more than half an hour.

People leaving Wuhan on the morning of January 23 told Caijing that they had been waiting in line for an hour and a half at gongjialing toll station. Gongjialing Toll Station is located in Wuhan-hubei Expressway, which is the highway from Zuoling of Wuhan to Huahu of Ezhou.

The closure of the highway is imminent, after suspected cases of infection caused by self-driving trips. A suspected case of COVID-19 pneumonia has been found in Inner Mongolia Manzhouli, the People's Daily reported. The patient, a 30-year-old male who lives in Wuhan and is in the clothing business, drove to Manzhouli on the 21st and went directly to the Emergency Department of the Manzhouli People's Hospital.

As of 12:30 noon on January 23, "The temporary traffic control on the expressways due to fog has been completely lifted, and the highways throughout the province have resumed normal traffic, " read a recent post by the Hubei Expressway traffic police, no response yet.

On Weibo and other social media, netizens are stirring up a discussion about the license plate a for leaving Hubei. Some netizens have posted that, on the highway, just next to the CAR A, coordinates of Yibin; "closed city" is the result of Hubei a license plate surrounded the city below.

The city of Yichang in Hubei Province announced on January 22 that special manual passageways will be set up at the exit of various toll booth to check the temperature of drivers and passengers of Hubei a license plate vehicles entering the city through the expressway.

The cities around Wuhan can not be left alone. Dongfeng travel-related personnel to "finance and Economics" reporters, in addition to the platform for Wuhan vehicles issued 84 disinfection solution and other equipment, neighboring Xiangyang, Shiyan has also designated a plan.

In addition to the highway, there are national roads and village roads for travel. A local Wuhan resident expressed doubts to "CAIJING" reporter, although the high-speed closure, but the national road and Village Road How to do? Wuhan special terrain, I do not know whether the bridge and tunnel closed?

As of 2:00 p.m. on January 23, CCTV reporters learned from the Hubei Provincial Highway Administration that the entrances to Gongjialing, Xiaojunshan, Hannan, Beihu, Hanayama, Baiquan, Qinglong and Xihu stations in Hubei Province were closed. The Beijing–Hong Kong–Macau Expressway of the Toll Gates at Wuhan West, Wuhan North, Caidian District and Yong'an will be closed. Other highway crossings out of Wuhan have also been closed.

Long-distance passenger transport has been suspended since 10:00 this morning, with online taxi-hailing and taxi-hailing becoming an important means of cross-city public transport.

Ticktock free ride response "CAIJING" reporter said, 10 o'clock, ticktock trip to start a response, has temporarily closed Wuhan Intercity Free Ride and city free ride channel.

LEFT-BEHIND CITIZENS: I will not leave Wuhan at this time

"The quick-frozen dumplings seem to be out of stock. There are only two bags left, and a family can eat one bag for every three meals. ". A resident who stayed behind in Wuhan had just eaten his first meal after the siege.

When something you're used to suddenly shuts down, it can be overwhelming. Quick-frozen dumplings, open the e-commerce shopping platform, but found that some have not received the order, has also become Schrodinger's express delivery. Going out to the market, I passed the small supermarket downstairs. The shopkeeper said that the stock had been sold out.

Citizens wearing masks and people who do not usually buy food are once again entering the market. A man named Guan, who is in Wuhan University town, told Caijing that the price of the vegetable market has increased by about 50% since he learned of the news of the closure of the city. "The price of Chinese cabbage is 5 yuan a catty, 10 yuan a catty for a thousand pieces and 5 yuan a catty for Vegetable Moss. "

Mr. Guan revealed that the small takeaway seems to be closed, but the larger ones, such as KFC and chicken from the countryside, and a few of the dining halls are still open. For this reason, he has stored up supplies for a month.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
Business trip in Wuhan encounter the city of Mr. Guan said, vegetables some difficult to buy, the price rose nearly 50% 

The Wuhan new pneumonia prevention and Control Headquarters issued notice No. 2 that the closure of the Lihan corridor is necessary to stop the spread of the epidemic, with Wuhan's commodities, food, medical protection supplies and so on being well-stocked and in smooth supply. Please do not panic, do not have to hoard, so as not to cause unnecessary waste.

He, who often travels to Wuhan on business, met with the "closure of the city" during the first Spring Festival in Wuhan. "As long as the supply of basic water and electricity networks is OK, logistics and express delivery can maintain a basic, I think the impact on most residents should not be too great.

Earlier in the day, the municipal epidemic prevention and Control Headquarters announced (No. 1) that starting from 10:00 on January 23, the city's public transport will be suspended, and taxis will become an important way for some citizens to travel.

To this end, the Wuhan Passenger Management Office told the majority of taxi drivers, and strictly prohibit the opportunity to misappropriate money and Carpool, refused to carry, detour and other illegal operations. Violators will be punished to the maximum extent possible. Local ride-hailing services have also begun to respond, with cancelled trips generally exempted from liability.

Dongfeng travel related personnel responded to Caijing reporter that Wuhan's operating vehicles are equipped with 84 disinfectants and are washed every day; if the driver is diagnosed, during treatment and isolation, the rental contract is suspended and the rent is waived.

Bike sharing may be an important supplement to getting around the city, said a passenger who arrived at Hankou Railway Station in the morning and cycled nearly five kilometers to his home as there were hundreds of people waiting in line to catch a cab.

At 12:55 on Jan. 23, CAIJING reporters used Didi Chuxing to try to hail a taxi at Hankou Railway Station, showing a queue of 116th, with an estimated response time of more than an hour. There were 40 people waiting in line at the Wuhan Railway Station, with an estimated response time of 40 minutes.

Residents in the surrounding areas of Wuhan have also gradually put on alert. A resident surnamed Li Shiyan said that Shiyan also attaches great importance to epidemic prevention. Residents in urban areas have a strong awareness of epidemic prevention, while those in the counties and urban areas under its jurisdiction are a little worse. Only a very small number of people wear masks on the streets, after the closure of the city, masks were in short supply in Shiyan, where many pharmacies could no longer buy them.

Dongfeng travel-related personnel to "finance and Economics" reporters, in addition to the platform for Wuhan vehicles issued 84 disinfection solution and other equipment, neighboring Xiangyang, Shiyan also designated the plan.

"Most of the returnees will be back around twenty-five on the 12th of December, " Ms. Li said, adding that counties have paid attention to the situation of the returnees. But the price of food is basically normal, in previous years also before this time rise, but so far has not been affected by the epidemic.

In the interview, the most left-behind residents of Wuhan said that, although also a little afraid, but hope not to cause panic.

"I will not leave Wuhan at this time, " a local reporter stationed on the front line told Caijing. Although the situation in Wuhan is now grim, the central committee and the Wuhan Municipal Government decided to close down the city, to keep the virus from spreading to other cities. Wuhan is now a strong determination to break the wrist.

(CAIJING reporter Wang Binbin and new media operations editor Yang Peiqian contributed reporting.)
